I reviewed the reported the child pornography files and determined that four (4) files constitute child pornography as it is defined under Maryland Law. After reviewing the reported media provided by Synchronoss Technologies, Inc, I determined that the five (5) files reported contained a total of fifteen (15) images identified as child pornography. The CyberTipline Report indicated that the Synchronoss Technologies account associated with 443-754-5748 was utilized to upload the reported child pornography files. I conducted a query of the phone number through an open-source database and determined that it is registered to Verizon Wireless and geo-locates to Salisbury, Wicomico County, Maryland. I transmitted an investigative subpoena request to the Wicomico County Office of the States Attorney for Verizon and submitted a written preservation request for the reported account to Synchronoss Technologies, Inc. Case open, investigation continuing.
